	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Memphis</placeName> <date>July 1 1860</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Rev Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>It is long that I have <del>not</del> received any lines from you.<lb/>  I suppose you are very busy&#44; especially <del>that</del> as the day<lb/> draws near when the <hi rend="underline">board of delegates</hi> will reassemble.<lb/>  I wish&#44; I could be present&#44; but business etc with&#45;<lb/>holds me of enjoying the sight of men who still act in<lb/> behalf of that time honored Judaism.  I wonder sir&#33;<lb/> how it was and still is possible&#44; that you could<lb/>&#59; fight our battles so long without retreating a single moment&#44;<lb/> after having been so often insulted by those <hi rend="underline">renegades</hi><lb/> and so little supported by those for whom you appeared<lb/> as champion.  Is there no hope that you and the<lb/> cause you represent will triumph&#63;  I wish I<lb/> had the power to write with such facility as you have.<lb/>  I would assist you with all my might.  Dear Sir<lb/> if there will not be made a decisive step&#44; those<lb/> infidels will promulgate their nefarious doctrines&#44; the<lb/> people will swallow the gilded pill offered to them<lb/> by the pseudo&#45;doctors.  I have tried and will<lb/> still try to keep them out of our regions&#44; though<lb/> they have triumphed for a while.  <persName>Wise</persName> is trying to<lb/> get one of his emissaries here&#44; and I believe he<lb/> will succeed for the infidels stand on the lead<lb/> now.  I will write you all about it after<lb/> a while.  If you find it worthy of appearing<lb/> in your valuable paper&#44; insert the <sic>the</sic> following few<lb/> words&#8212;Why <hi rend="underline">do we hide</hi> it&#63;</p>
		</body>
